<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 14-year-old boy has been arrested on suspicion of attempted murder after two teenagers were stabbed in the chest.</p>

<p>Two 16-year-olds were stabbed during an incident in Tilehurst, Berkshire, at around 11.30pm on Saturday.</p>

<p>One of the boys remains in hospital in a serious but stable condition, while the other victim has been discharged. </p>

<p>Police have arrested a 14-year-old boy after two teenagers were stabbed during an incident in Tilehurst, Berkshire, at around 11.30pm on Saturday night (scene pictured above)</p>

<p>Police confirmed they launched an attempted murder investigation on Sunday after the horrific attack </p>

<p>Police launched an attempted murder investigation on Sunday and Thames Valley Police confirmed the arrest on Monday evening.</p>

<p>Investigators had identified a man who was seen running away from the scene with others following the attack, who were described as wearing dark clothing and face masks.</p>

<p>Senior investigating officer Detective Chief Inspector Mike Hall, based at Newbury police station, said: 'We remain in the early stages of this investigation, but have now made one arrest. </p>

<p>Investigators identified a man who was seen running away from the scene with others following the attack, who were all described as wearing dark clothing and face masks</p>

<p>'I would ask people not to speculate as to the circumstances surrounding this incident, but I would like to renew my appeal for anybody who witnessed what happened on Saturday night who have not already made contact with police to please do so.</p>

<p>'We have been very grateful for the support the local community have shown so far and appreciate all those who have come forward with information.</p>

<p>'I would also like to reiterate my previous request not to share any images or footage you may have on social media, but please report this to police.'</p>

<p>Anyone with any information should call 101, quoting reference 43200286779 or make a report online.</p>

<p>Witness can also call the independent charity Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.   </p>

<p>One of the boys remains in hospital in a serious but stable condition, while the other victim has since been discharged from hospital </p>
